tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE online_resources (
  resource_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  resource_title VARCHAR(255),
  resource_type VARCHAR(50),
  resource_link VARCHAR(255),
  created_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE resources (
    resource_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    resource_name VARCHAR(255),
    resource_type VARCHAR(50),
    url VARCHAR(255),
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

CREATE TABLE student_materials (
    student_material_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id UUID,
    resource_id UUID,
    progress DECIMAL,
    is_completed BOOLEAN,
    completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

CREATE TABLE student_records (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
    subject_id INT REFERENCES subjects(subject_id),
    resource_id INT REFERENCES resources(resource_id),
    date_accessed DATE
);

CREATE TABLE reviews (
  review_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  student_id INT REFERENCES students(student_id),
  resource_id INT REFERENCES resources(resource_id),
  rating INT,
  review_text TEXT
);
CREATE TABLE Courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY, course_name VARCHAR(255), instructor VARCHAR(255), enrolled_students INT, course_description TEXT)
CREATE TABLE Students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_name VARCHAR(255), email VARCHAR(255), joining_date DATE, grade_level VARCHAR(50)
CREATE TABLE Materials (material_id INT PRIMARY KEY, material_name VARCHAR(255), material_type VARCHAR(50), upload_date DATE, course_id INT)
CREATE TABLE Enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, enrollment_date DATE)
CREATE TABLE Reviews (review_id INT PRIMARY KEY, student_id INT, course_id INT, rating INT, review_text TEXT)
